{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Biscuit Base","content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease and line base and sides of a spring form tin (Ø 26 cm).","Place butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add biscuits then chop <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to prepared tin, pressing down with the back of a spoon forming an even layer over base, then push mixture evenly halfway up sides of tin. Set aside in fridge. Clean mixing bowl and make filling."]},{"title":"White Chocolate Filling","content":["Place chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add cream then melt <b>3 min 30 sec\/50°C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add cream cheese and sugar then beat <b>20 sec\/speed 5.5<b>.","Add eggs, vanilla extract and salt then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>. Place tin on a large baking tray then pour mixture into tin over biscuit base. Bake for 1 hour (160°C) until browned and risen with a slight wobble.","Leave in tin on a wire rack to cool completely - the cheesecake will sink considerably (see tip). Once cool, chill in fridge for at least 4 hours. Meanwhile, make caramel sauce."]},{"title":"Caramel Sauce","content":["Place soft brown sugar, cream, butter and lemon juice in mixing bowl then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool.","Once cool and cheesecake has set, pour caramel sauce over centre of cheesecake. Leave at room temperature for 1 hour before removing from tin and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Biscuit Base","content":["90 g unsalted butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","280 g digestive biscuits"]},{"title":"White Chocolate Filling","content":["230 g white chocolate, small pieces or callets","110 g double cream","700 g cream cheese","220 g granulated sugar","5 large eggs","1 tsp vanilla extract","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Caramel Sauce","content":["140 g soft brown sugar","200 g double cream","30 g unsalted butter","1 tsp lemon juice"]}],"id":"r137746","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KFCwWCkviJs\/XZWrd4oC4eI\/AAAAAAAAfnw\/PELmb4nY2okPS3YYnp7u5T5KkIx8678KwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_m3GGrOI-kMxGJOPa.png","title":"Baked White Chocolate Caramel Cheesecake","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.3 g","fat":"46.3 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"43.6 g","calories":"2579 kJ \/ 616 kcal"},"usefulItems":"spring form tin (Ø 26 cm), large baking tray, wire rack, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Run a knife around the edge of the cheesecake as soon as it comes out of the oven - this will prevent cracks appearing in the surface."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","6h 20m","16 slices"]}